At first my daughter didn't like this video, even though she loves elmo. But now it's one of her favorites. She's a few months away from being 2. She loves dancing and humming to the songs and tries to mimic the 'elmo slide' and the 'snazzy shuffle'. It's helping to teach her through the songs and dances about the names of her body. It would help to teach Spanish if she was already speaking English, but she still dances to the music no matter what language they're speaking in.
My twins LOVE this video.  They loved it when they first saw it at 3 months of age (it was the only thing on TV that caught their attrention) and they still love it now at 10 months.
My granddaughter loves this!!  She's only 14 months and she points the remote to the TV and says "Bobo" which is Elmo!

Some songs are better than others. I wish there was a menu function so that you could skip over less preferred songs and skip to favorites. I also wish there was a list of the songs on the description of the video. My little one loves to watch the songs on sesamestreet.org, and we purchased this video to be able to watch some of them while on the go - however it would have been nice to have a heads up as to which songs were included.

This is a great compilation that really keeps my 13 month old son's interest. We've had this DVD for a few months so he's familiar with the songs now and as soon as he hears the intro music he gets excited. He especially loves the songs with Sugarland, Elvis Costello, Taye Diggs, Bruno Mars, and he gets excited over the short skits as well. I personally love the DVD; mostly because he does but it's also so catchy, I find myself singing the songs even after the DVD is finished lol.

Also, as always all Elmo is grand for the family.
My little watch the video everyday and enjoy the sing-a-longs!!
My son loves Elmo, so of course we had to get this. Its pretty cute. I wish there was more singing in it though.

My 22 month old loves this dvd - with the only exception being the Justin Beiber "measure" song - she literally makes me fast forward thru that one. ("No Elmo" she says.) It's got some of my favorite performers, which makes it it all the more enjoyable for me! Train, Sugarland, Taye Diggs, Melissa McCarthy are only a few of those featured! Am now wanting to look into 1&2 - if they're anything like this one, it's a home run!
My 12 month old absolutely loves this video and that is enough for me.  One of the better ones with better music.
My 11-month-old son loves this DVD!  He will watch the whole thing with a big smile on his face and he will clap along.  He never gets tired of it!

My 14 month old son loves this DVD. He's pretty much moved on and bored with the Baby Genius videos, now he's into Elmo and Mickey Mouse Clubhouse. This DVD keeps his attention nearly the whole time. Its almost all singing - not much talking. I love the more recent celebs on this video - Michael Bubble, Alicia Keys, Nora Jones, Melissa McCarthy, Drew Breeze, etc. Really cute Elmo Slide and Elmo's Got the Moves segments. This video doesn't drive me completely nuts which is a plus. (PS - I hate the Elvis Costello segment - drives me bonkers, he sucks!!)
my son loves this - collection of lotsa Elmo songs
